We recommended to the management to:
Direct the MHO to:
Create a policy/guideline for the qualified beneficiaries of free drugs, medicines, medical and dental supplies, and medical laboratory procedures;
Establish internal control for the issuance of drugs, medicines, medical and dental supplies and conduct medical laboratory procedures by having a duly approved request form before issuance of supplies or conduct of medical laboratory procedures;
Prepare weekly RSMI to record receipts and issuance/utilization of inventory, and submit to GSO for monitoring and to the accounting office for the recording of expense; and,
conduct of semi-annual physical inventory count.;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to ensure completeness of supporting documents relevant to the recording of transactions, such that recording of related expenses for drugs and medicines and laboratory supplies should be supported with RIS and RSMI upon issuance of supplies, submitted by the MHO; and
Direct the GSO to assist MHO in the conduct of semi-annual physical inventory count.
Direct the MHO and the GSO to ensure that the Office of the Municipal Accountant is notified whenever there are donations of drugs and medicines. The latter must also ensure that all donations of drugs and medicines are properly accounted for and recorded in the books of accounts. Similarly, the GSO and the MHO must accurately record and monitor all donations. The issuance of these donations shall be processed through the RIS, which will be attached to SSMIs that are separately prepared and submitted to the accounting unit.
Furthermore, these donations should also be subjected to a semiannual inventory count by the inventory committee.

We recommended to the management to:
Recompute the salaries of the mentioned employees considering approve leave beyond leave credit balance as LWOP, refund any overpayment of salaries, and make adjustment to the posted earned and availed leave credits;
Deduct from VL the excess of nine (9) days over the maximum allowed 3 days of SPL;
Coordinate with HRIS provider to incorporate internal control in the system with regard to limit in SPL and other leave benefits.
To monitor leave balances and establish preventive measures for sound management; and,
Make an internal policy with regards to the inclusion/exclusion of employees to the general payroll to avoid future case of the scenario above.

We recommended to the management to perform the following:
1)	Require the Inventory and Disposal Committee to hasten the inspection, appraisal and disposal of those identified unserviceable heavy equipment and other motor vehicles owned by the LGU-Kalilangan, strictly adhering with the disposal procedures of the above-mentioned applicable rules and regulations;

2)	Submit immediately to the audit team for auditorial review the complete documentary requirements prior review and inspection by the COA Regional Office No. 10’s Regional Technical Audit Group (RTAG);

3)	Resort to proper disposition thru public auction or to other mode of disposal, if deemed appropriate, subject to applicable rules and regulations;

4)	Require the Municipal Accountant to drop from the books of accounts those properties already disposed thru a drawing of Journal Entry Voucher, to be substantiated with complete documentation subject for post-audit; and,

5)	Treat any proceeds from sale of unserviceable properties as a general income under the General Fund subject for supplemental appropriation to finance priority programs and projects of the municipality.

We recommended to the management to require the following:

Reconstitute an Inventory Committee to conduct physical count of all Local Road Networks (LRN) and ensure the preparation of the Report on the Physical Count of the Local Road Network (RPCLRN) at least annually;
The General Services Officer to prepare and maintain a Report on Local Road Networks (RLRN), maintain road map, and keep a complete LRN Property Card for all roads and its components;
The Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
The Municipal Accountant to effect adjusting journal entries, if warranted, duly supported with the working paper on the distribution of costs upon completion of the above-required reports, including the adjustments for depreciation. Moreover, disclose the total road network system in the Notes to the Financial Statements of the LGU in the prescribed form as required in Annex B of COA Circular 2015-002.

