We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to ensure to expedite the implementation of all programs, activities and projects under the 20% Development Fund, including those in prior years. Moreover, submit a valid justification on the incurrence of delays in the full implementation of projects undertaken thru administration and thru straight contract by contractors and on the laxity of management in the monitoring of its projects.

For projects undertaken by contractors, the following procedures available for management should be resorted: 

Demand those contractors to hastily complete their pending projects as soon as possible, without prejudice to the imposition of liquidated damages until the works have been completed;

2)	Considering that the posted performance bond had already expired and not forfeited by management, require the erring contractors to post another performance security equivalent to the value of the unperformed work/s;

3) Require the Municipal Accountant to compute for liquidated damages and deduct the same from the final billing of the contractor with corresponding brief explanation on the face of the disbursement vouchers;

4) Demand the contractors in default to post a new and valid surety bond in lieu of the released retentions in CY 2019. The Municipal Mayor’s Office, in coordination with the Municipal Engineer and the Municipal Accountant, to strictly monitor the expiration of surety bonds every year for warranty purposes to cover the uncorrected discovered defects and third-party liabilities prior to project acceptance;

5)  If the said delayed projects will not be continued by the contractors, adopt termination of contract and forfeiture of performance security. After termination, take over the contract or resort to any of other alternative methods of procurement provided under R.A. No. 9184 and its 2016 revised Rules and Regulations. Thereafter, issue a blacklisting order to sanction the erring contractors in order to prohibit the latter to participate in the bidding of any government projects/contracts;

6) Implement an effective monitoring and evaluation control on the status of implementation of infrastructure and other projects by organizing a Local Project Monitoring Committee pursuant to DILG Memorandum Circulars No. 2004-78 and 2019-188 dated 22 June 2004 and 14 November 2019, respectively; and,

7) Require the Municipal Engineer to ascertain the correctness and completeness of information presented in the Quarterly Report of Publicized Projects/Programs/Activities, not only disclosing those projects with pending status but also for all projects to be undertaken by management during the year.

