We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to require the Head of Human Resource Management Unit (HRMU) and Municipal Accountant to:
Submit immediately to COA the following required documents to support the disbursed transactions, in which failure to do so may warrant audit suspension or disallowance, as the case may be:
Certifications from the HRMU Head justifying the necessity to grant the monetization using the sick leave credit balances, supported with valid and justifiable reasons from those who requested the monetization, by taking into consideration the allowable justifications as enumerated in  the amended Section 23, Rule XVI of the Omnibus Rules on Leave;
Leave cards duly certified by the HRMU Head for those who have requested monetization;
Justification as to the incurrence of excessive payments of monetization to the said employees; and
Justification on allowing payment of monetization to the mentioned employee even without enough available balance of leave credits, thus incurred negative balance on such leave credits.
Discontinue the improper practice of granting monetization charged to the remaining five-day vacation leave balances without valid reasons of such use;
Discontinue the grant of monetization of leave credits to top government officials without first giving preference/priority to those employees holding positions below salary grade 19;
Reconcile all leave balances, especially those with negative balances. Update all leave cards of officials and employees and assure that every request for monetization must be posted to leave cards prudently and conscientiously;
Adhere strictly to the applicable rules and regulations governing the monetization of leave credits of government officials and employees.

